n_{\text{odd places}} = \frac{4!}{2!\cdot 2!} = 6.
n_{\text{even places}} = \frac{4!}{3!\cdot 1!} = 4.
n_{\text{total}} = n_{\text{odd places}}\cdot n_{\text{even places}} = 6\cdot 4 = 24.
